===Overview===
The national defense of [[Costa Verde]] is ensured by the National Army of Costa Verde, with [[Andres Camarro (Earth-616)|General Andres Camarro]] at its head. They protected the government of [[Juan Elmirez (Earth-616)|President Juan Elmirez]].{{r|Marvel Atlas #2|; [[Costa Verde]]'s entry}}

===Rodrigo Valdez and Carlos Gormaz's rebellion===
[[Rodrigo Valdez (Earth-616)|Rodrigo Valdez]] and [[Carlos Gormaz (Earth-616)|Carlos Gormaz]] led a revolt, and used the [[Arthur Parks (Earth-616)|Living Laser]] to decimate the government's forces, before being stopped by the [[Avengers (Earth-616)|Avengers]].{{r|Marvel Atlas #2|; [[Costa Verde]]'s entry}}

===El Lobo's rebellion===
After revolutionary leader [[Ramiro Xuc (Earth-616)|El Lobo]] controlled [[Pyreus Kril (Earth-616)|Firelord]] and [[Thor Odinson (Earth-616)|Thor]] for a time, they eventually regained their senses, captured El Lobo and his men (including [[Manuel Hidalgo (Earth-616)|Manuel Hidalgo]] and [[Carmen Escudero (Earth-616)|Gypsy]]) and delivered them to the army.{{r|Marvel Atlas #2|; [[Costa Verde]]'s entry}}

===Peace===
====Kulan Gath====
During the subsequent period of peace, an army division was sent to investigate explosions and disappearances in the [[Kamekeri Valley]], and was close to enter the area controlled by [[Kulan Gath (Impostor) (Earth-616)|Kulan Gath]], a zone in which entering would had turned them into barbarian soldiers loyal to Gath.{{r|Avengers Vol 3 29}}

After having trouble convincing President Elmirez and General Camarro, [[Anthony Stark (Earth-616)|Iron Man]] and [[Janet Van Dyne (Earth-616)|Wasp]] managed to, and using a trick from the [[Wanda Maximoff (Earth-616)|Scarlet Witch]] to shield the army from Kulan Gath's spell. The army consequently entered the city, but the brawl became confuse as Kulan Gath invoked [[N'Garai]] and turned part of the army by directly casting the spell upon them. [[Maria de Guadalupe Santiago (Earth-616)|Silverclaw]]'s call upon the transformed locals to remember [[Peliali (Earth-616)|Peliali]] (the volcano goddess protector of the [[Kamekeri (Earth-616)|Kamekeri people]] that Kulan Gath was upon to sacrifice to obtain godhood), Gath was eventually defeated and the people and [[Kamekeri Village|village]] returned to their original states.{{r|Avengers Vol 3 30}}
